WEBVTT

﻿1
00:01:14.257 --> 00:01:17.886
Commander General.
you are called to answer

2
00:01:17.969 --> 00:01:19.846
for the escape
of the prisoner. Tamacti Jun.

3
00:01:19.930 --> 00:01:22.307
Tamacti Jun was not my prisoner.

4
00:01:22.390 --> 00:01:26.228
- But Baba Voss was.
- Baba Voss was an enemy of the Republic.

5
00:01:26.895 --> 00:01:28.355
Who should have been put on trial

6
00:01:28.438 --> 00:01:31.608
and executed expeditiously.
as the law requires.

7
00:01:31.691 --> 00:01:35.570
Had you done that.
he never would have had the opportunity

8
00:01:35.654 --> 00:01:37.280
to escape with Tamacti Jun.

9
00:01:37.364 --> 00:01:39.616
The Witchfinder was a potential source

10
00:01:39.698 --> 00:01:43.787
of great intelligence for us
on the Payan queen's larger strategy

11
00:01:43.870 --> 00:01:45.330
and military assets.

12
00:01:45.413 --> 00:01:48.250
Do you have any idea
how they managed to escape?

13
00:01:48.792 --> 00:01:52.170
Such a devastating breach
in our security is unheard of.

14
00:01:52.754 --> 00:01:55.924
They must have had help.
Someone on the inside.

15
00:01:56.883 --> 00:02:00.053
Then we must ferret out
the traitor. or traitors.

16
00:02:00.136 --> 00:02:01.388
and make an example of them.

17
00:02:01.471 --> 00:02:05.308
If there are traitors. I will find them.

18
00:02:06.893 --> 00:02:10.730
General Voss. you have served this council

19
00:02:10.814 --> 00:02:13.859
with great honor and valor for many years.

20
00:02:13.942 --> 00:02:16.862
but your obsession
with the rumors of the return of sight.

21
00:02:16.945 --> 00:02:21.783
your personal vendetta with your brother.
they must be put aside.

22
00:02:21.867 --> 00:02:23.994
The Ganites grow
ever more bold in the west.

23
00:02:24.077 --> 00:02:25.579
You are our greatest tactician.

24
00:02:25.662 --> 00:02:29.583
We need you focused
on the true threats to this republic.

25
00:02:30.542 --> 00:02:32.294
Do you understand?

26
00:02:36.840 --> 00:02:41.761
Yes. I understand. sir.

27
00:02:49.227 --> 00:02:51.354
I want you to question every guard
who came in contact

28
00:02:51.438 --> 00:02:52.856
with Baba Voss or Tamacti Jun.

29
00:02:52.939 --> 00:02:55.192
I already did. sir.
They didn't have anything useful to offer.

30
00:02:55.275 --> 00:02:59.696
Well. then question them again.
Someone will break.

31
00:03:00.197 --> 00:03:01.198
Yes. sir.

32
00:04:40.005 --> 00:04:42.174
Who's there?

33
00:04:43.675 --> 00:04:45.468
- It's okay.
- Oloman?

34
00:04:45.552 --> 00:04:46.553
It's okay.

35
00:04:58.982 --> 00:05:00.317
Another bad dream?

36
00:05:02.444 --> 00:05:03.695
You don't understand.

37
00:05:05.155 --> 00:05:06.740
The dreams are beautiful.

38
00:05:08.158 --> 00:05:12.746
I can see the world. my children.

39
00:05:14.706 --> 00:05:17.000
It's when I wake up
that the nightmare starts.

40
00:05:20.003 --> 00:05:22.172
We're still here. Father.

41
00:05:23.423 --> 00:05:24.673
We'd never leave you.

42
00:05:29.721 --> 00:05:31.598
Have you found a way to fix this?

43
00:05:32.307 --> 00:05:35.101
I know it can be done
with the right equipment.

44
00:05:36.436 --> 00:05:39.773
We simply don't have the machines.
the technology to do the things you ask.

45
00:05:52.077 --> 00:05:54.496
Have you forgotten everything
that I taught you?

46
00:05:58.917 --> 00:06:01.169
It's been my life's work
to build this place.

47
00:06:03.338 --> 00:06:07.175
Through setbacks and overwhelming odds.
I persevered.

48
00:06:09.052 --> 00:06:10.262
Now you…

49
00:06:14.140 --> 00:06:16.184
You must rise to the challenge.

50
00:06:17.143 --> 00:06:21.481
Take what seems impossible
and make it possible.

51
00:06:23.108 --> 00:06:27.320
You must dedicate your every
waking moment to restoring my sight

52
00:06:27.404 --> 00:06:29.823
so that I can fulfill my destiny.

53
00:06:31.199 --> 00:06:32.993
Now. it won't happen overnight.

54
00:06:34.202 --> 00:06:37.956
and I was wrong to make you feel
like it should.

55
00:06:39.916 --> 00:06:43.336
We must both settle in and persevere.

56
00:06:44.504 --> 00:06:46.173
No matter how long it takes.

57
00:06:49.634 --> 00:06:50.844
Yes. Father.

58
00:06:51.928 --> 00:06:52.929
All right.

59
00:06:54.472 --> 00:06:57.184
Now. your morning report?

60
00:06:58.351 --> 00:06:59.227
Now?

61
00:06:59.311 --> 00:07:01.438
Our work here continues. does it not?

62
00:07:03.690 --> 00:07:04.858
Of course it does. it's just...

63
00:07:04.941 --> 00:07:09.446
I may be injured.
but I am not compromised.

64
00:07:09.529 --> 00:07:13.283
And you shouldn't treat me as such.
or the children might follow suit.

65
00:07:14.034 --> 00:07:15.452
And the Trivantians…

66
00:07:18.997 --> 00:07:21.750
The Trivantians…

67
00:07:21.833 --> 00:07:23.502
They must not know of my injury.

68
00:07:24.169 --> 00:07:26.505
It is their fear of my abilities
that keeps them in check.

69
00:07:26.588 --> 00:07:27.672
Do you understand?

70
00:07:30.634 --> 00:07:31.635
Yes. Father.

71
00:07:34.137 --> 00:07:35.138
Good.

72
00:07:36.306 --> 00:07:40.810
Then… your morning report.

73
00:07:44.648 --> 00:07:49.402
Well. Nonni has moved on
to quadratic equations.

74
00:07:51.071 --> 00:07:52.489
She's very smart.

75
00:07:52.739 --> 00:07:55.367
I started her on the text
that you suggested.

76
00:07:55.450 --> 00:07:57.661
She took to it like a moth to a flame.

77
00:08:21.268 --> 00:08:24.896
They left before the agreed-upon time.
Something must have happened.

78
00:08:24.980 --> 00:08:26.773
We don't have time to search for them.

79
00:08:26.857 --> 00:08:30.402
Our priority must be
to find Princess Maghra.

80
00:08:34.531 --> 00:08:37.033
Princess Maghra? What is he talking about?

81
00:08:40.036 --> 00:08:44.499
If he is to be believed.
your mother is sister to the queen.

82
00:08:46.918 --> 00:08:51.006
- Queen Kane? That is ridiculous.
- I know it is hard to believe.

83
00:08:51.089 --> 00:08:55.135
What's hard to believe is that you didn't
tear him to pieces the moment you met him.

84
00:08:55.635 --> 00:08:56.970
I did consider it.

85
00:08:58.805 --> 00:09:01.558
- This could be a trap. Papa.
- Yes.

86
00:09:01.641 --> 00:09:04.227
And yet you allow him to lead us. Why?

87
00:09:05.478 --> 00:09:08.565
For the same reasons I came
to find you in Trivantes.

88
00:09:09.858 --> 00:09:11.401
She's my wife. Haniwa.

89
00:09:11.902 --> 00:09:14.154
It's the only woman I will ever love.

90
00:09:14.237 --> 00:09:16.239
And if there's the smallest chance
that she's alive…

91
00:09:16.323 --> 00:09:17.532
I understand.

92
00:09:21.244 --> 00:09:25.582
But if he is lying.
then I want to kill him with you.

93
00:09:26.833 --> 00:09:28.210
I give you my word.

94
00:09:29.753 --> 00:09:34.132
And if he is not lying.
then my mother is a Payan princess.

95
00:09:34.216 --> 00:09:35.383
How could that be?

96
00:09:37.219 --> 00:09:38.553
I do not have answers.

97
00:09:39.971 --> 00:09:42.140
I trust your mother will explain
once we find her.

98
00:09:43.433 --> 00:09:44.433
Come.

99
00:09:57.489 --> 00:09:59.699
Three horses. two dogs.

100
00:10:00.992 --> 00:10:03.036
- Trivantians?
- Witchfinders.

101
00:10:03.537 --> 00:10:04.746
If they hurt my son...

102
00:10:04.829 --> 00:10:06.957
Witchfinders serve the pleasure
of the queen.

103
00:10:07.040 --> 00:10:09.751
If Maghra is with the queen.
then their orders will be

104
00:10:09.835 --> 00:10:12.045
to find and retrieve her children.

105
00:10:12.671 --> 00:10:14.756
- But the queen would have them burned.
- No.

106
00:10:15.340 --> 00:10:17.717
I learned that the queen issued
a new decree.

107
00:10:17.801 --> 00:10:20.512
The sighted are no longer
to be considered witches.

108
00:10:22.222 --> 00:10:23.473
So where do we go?

109
00:10:23.557 --> 00:10:27.269
East. There's a Witchfinder camp nearby.

110
00:10:27.769 --> 00:10:29.521
They'll know where the queen is settled.

111
00:10:31.773 --> 00:10:32.607
Pennsa.

112
00:10:32.691 --> 00:10:33.859
What?

113
00:10:34.359 --> 00:10:36.069
They took Kofun to Pennsa.

114
00:10:37.195 --> 00:10:39.406
- Did he leave you a sign?
- Yes.

115
00:10:40.490 --> 00:10:41.658
Pennsa.

116
00:10:42.158 --> 00:10:46.746
Highly fortified. prosperous.
strategically located.

117
00:10:47.372 --> 00:10:50.584
I would guess the queen
has consecrated a new capital.

118
00:11:09.561 --> 00:11:13.148
What is this vital matter
that couldn't wait. Lord Harlan?

119
00:11:13.231 --> 00:11:15.025
I don't mean to be alarmist.

120
00:11:15.108 --> 00:11:19.029
but when Your Majesty's
personal safety's at stake.

121
00:11:19.112 --> 00:11:21.990
I'd rather be guilty of overreacting
than complacency.

122
00:11:23.033 --> 00:11:25.410
Must everything with you include a speech?

123
00:11:26.745 --> 00:11:28.747
I'll keep it brief. I promise.

124
00:11:30.081 --> 00:11:32.250
I want you to hear this firsthand.

125
00:11:33.293 --> 00:11:36.922
I only ask that you stay very. very still.

126
00:11:37.923 --> 00:11:40.509
If he knows you're here.
I fear he won't speak freely.

127
00:11:41.968 --> 00:11:44.221
I'll be silent as a spider.

128
00:11:54.314 --> 00:11:59.945
Lord Harlan. this is Zechan.
the man who requested the audience.

129
00:12:00.445 --> 00:12:01.947
Thank you. Kerrigan.

130
00:12:13.667 --> 00:12:15.544
Is someone else in the room?

131
00:12:16.294 --> 00:12:19.714
A trusted servant loyal to me.

132
00:12:20.674 --> 00:12:22.467
Where are you from. Zechan?

133
00:12:23.969 --> 00:12:25.095
Kanzua. sir.

134
00:12:25.595 --> 00:12:28.598
And you were a palace sentry at Kanzua?

135
00:12:29.307 --> 00:12:30.851
Yes. sir. For over 20 years.

136
00:12:32.143 --> 00:12:35.063
So you were there
when the Trivantians attacked?

137
00:12:37.858 --> 00:12:40.026
I was there when Kanzua fell.

138
00:12:41.778 --> 00:12:45.949
But the thing of it is.
there was no attack.

139
00:12:47.993 --> 00:12:50.537
Then how did the dam come to be destroyed?

140
00:12:51.371 --> 00:12:53.123
I can't say for sure. sir.

141
00:12:53.206 --> 00:12:56.418
All I know is. there were no Trivantians.

142
00:12:57.878 --> 00:12:59.713
I don't understand.

143
00:13:02.007 --> 00:13:03.800
It was a regular day.

144
00:13:05.010 --> 00:13:06.428
Birds and wind.

145
00:13:07.554 --> 00:13:10.307
Not once did I hear the sound
of Trivantian stingers.

146
00:13:10.390 --> 00:13:11.766
No war cries.

147
00:13:14.060 --> 00:13:19.357
So if it wasn't the Trivantians.
who was responsible?

148
00:13:25.197 --> 00:13:27.407
You have to understand. sir.

149
00:13:27.490 --> 00:13:31.494
My father was a guard at Kanzua.
as was his father before him.

150
00:13:31.578 --> 00:13:33.788
We have served the monarchy
for generations.

151
00:13:33.872 --> 00:13:35.332
I understand. I understand.

152
00:13:42.464 --> 00:13:43.548
It's all right.

153
00:13:44.382 --> 00:13:46.176
Say what you came to say. soldier.

154
00:13:50.305 --> 00:13:55.393
I knew those buildings inside and out.
every passageway. who had access.

155
00:13:55.477 --> 00:13:58.772
And I believe that the only person
who could have released the waters…

156
00:14:02.400 --> 00:14:04.236
Was the queen herself.

157
00:15:06.339 --> 00:15:09.050
Lord Harlan. you do have a flair
for the dramatic.

158
00:15:10.051 --> 00:15:12.095
This kind of talk. you know…

159
00:15:13.180 --> 00:15:15.765
left unchecked.
it can spread like a plague.

160
00:15:17.726 --> 00:15:20.478
And if the people doubt
your account of Kanzua.

161
00:15:21.188 --> 00:15:23.690
they will doubt the sighted child
you spoke of.

162
00:15:24.191 --> 00:15:26.026
and your mandate from God.

163
00:15:28.028 --> 00:15:29.154
All of it.

164
00:15:33.325 --> 00:15:35.577
You will make sure that won't happen.

165
00:15:37.329 --> 00:15:39.748
It's the least I can do
if it threatens my queen.

166
00:15:40.248 --> 00:15:43.376
And just think
how much more vigilant I'd be

167
00:15:44.085 --> 00:15:46.421
if it threatened the sister
of my own wife.

168
00:15:50.008 --> 00:15:51.676
Urgent message for you. my queen.

169
00:15:53.595 --> 00:15:54.679
Come.

170
00:16:22.207 --> 00:16:24.876
Rest assured. Harlan.
you'll have your bride.

171
00:16:46.523 --> 00:16:51.027
Sibeth. please.
I have no fight left in me right now.

172
00:16:51.111 --> 00:16:53.488
Relax. Sister. I come bearing good news.

173
00:16:54.698 --> 00:16:56.491
Kofun has been found.

174
00:16:57.868 --> 00:17:00.704
My soldiers are making their way back here
with him as we speak.

175
00:17:00.787 --> 00:17:03.832
What? When will they arrive?

176
00:17:03.915 --> 00:17:06.168
What about Haniwa and Baba Voss?

177
00:17:06.751 --> 00:17:08.461
No sign of them. I'm afraid.

178
00:17:09.880 --> 00:17:10.964
That doesn't make sense.

179
00:17:11.047 --> 00:17:13.425
He would have kept them together
at all costs.

180
00:17:14.467 --> 00:17:16.928
Unless he no longer could.

181
00:17:18.805 --> 00:17:21.474
And now that Kofun will be joining us.

182
00:17:21.558 --> 00:17:24.186
we are faced with the issue of his safety.

183
00:17:24.686 --> 00:17:25.562
Safety?

184
00:17:25.645 --> 00:17:29.858
As you witnessed. it will take some time
before the people embrace the new way.

185
00:17:31.193 --> 00:17:33.820
You had no such concerns about Boots.

186
00:17:35.780 --> 00:17:36.990
Boots is nobody.

187
00:17:37.866 --> 00:17:39.659
Just the father of your child.

188
00:17:43.163 --> 00:17:44.247
What?

189
00:17:47.250 --> 00:17:49.794
I can hear your heartbeat
growing faster. Sibeth.

190
00:17:52.631 --> 00:17:54.299
But only your heart.

191
00:17:57.177 --> 00:17:58.428
The baby.

192
00:18:00.180 --> 00:18:01.806
You lost the baby.

193
00:18:04.935 --> 00:18:08.396
Sibeth. I'm so sorry.

194
00:18:44.349 --> 00:18:48.603
Your child returns
while mine has decided not to come at all.

195
00:18:51.022 --> 00:18:53.692
Which does put us
in a somewhat difficult position.

196
00:18:56.236 --> 00:18:58.989
If word gets out that I'm not with child.

197
00:18:59.489 --> 00:19:01.950
the protection of sighted children
will be called into question

198
00:19:02.033 --> 00:19:03.910
even more than it already is.

199
00:19:03.994 --> 00:19:06.162
Kofun's safety will not be ensured.

200
00:19:06.872 --> 00:19:09.082
I don't understand this conversation.

201
00:19:09.165 --> 00:19:12.335
- Are you threatening my son?
- On the contrary.

202
00:19:12.419 --> 00:19:15.005
I'll do everything in my power
to protect my nephew.

203
00:19:15.755 --> 00:19:20.218
But if the people rise against me.
against us.

204
00:19:21.178 --> 00:19:23.221
there'll be no one left to protect him.

205
00:19:24.306 --> 00:19:25.765
This is about Harlan.

206
00:19:27.142 --> 00:19:31.271
An alliance with Lord Harlan guarantees us
control over a united military

207
00:19:31.354 --> 00:19:34.691
that will serve as the ultimate deterrent
to any talk of revolution.

208
00:19:34.774 --> 00:19:38.403
Why are you so insistent on this?
What aren't you telling me?

209
00:19:43.950 --> 00:19:46.620
Apparently. there are survivors of Kanzua.

210
00:19:49.206 --> 00:19:51.833
- If word spreads…
- Word will spread.

211
00:19:51.917 --> 00:19:55.962
The only question is how well positioned
we will be to quell any unrest

212
00:19:56.046 --> 00:19:58.256
to assert our authority when it does.

213
00:19:59.716 --> 00:20:05.138
A man in Harlan's position.
he could pour the water or fan flames.

214
00:20:05.222 --> 00:20:06.890
depending on where his interests lie.

215
00:20:06.973 --> 00:20:10.727
And right now. what he wants is you.

216
00:20:13.730 --> 00:20:16.691
Sister. I know what I'm asking of you.

217
00:20:17.192 --> 00:20:19.402
- I wouldn't ask it. but...
- Shh. Just... Just…

218
00:20:41.925 --> 00:20:42.926
Fine.

219
00:20:46.388 --> 00:20:47.556
Fine.

220
00:20:47.639 --> 00:20:53.770
I'll agree to this charade
as long as Harlan understands

221
00:20:53.854 --> 00:20:56.398
it's simply an arrangement of convenience.

222
00:20:59.651 --> 00:21:01.361
As all marriages are.

223
00:21:28.513 --> 00:21:31.933
I still can't imagine
my mother as a princess.

224
00:21:33.101 --> 00:21:35.729
Maghra Kane was born to rule.

225
00:21:35.812 --> 00:21:37.647
Her father's daughter in every way.

226
00:21:39.191 --> 00:21:41.193
Yet you hunted her like an animal.

227
00:21:41.276 --> 00:21:42.277
No.

228
00:21:42.360 --> 00:21:46.573
My charge was to find the witch.
Jerlamarel. and then his children.

229
00:21:47.365 --> 00:21:49.784
Maghra was believed to be dead.

230
00:21:51.995 --> 00:21:55.290
- We should camp here.
- We just started walking.

231
00:21:55.790 --> 00:21:59.085
It's a difficult passage up
through the foothills.

232
00:22:00.003 --> 00:22:01.630
Your father will need rest.

233
00:22:02.130 --> 00:22:03.882
Do not speak for me. Witchfinder.

234
00:22:04.382 --> 00:22:06.384
Okay. then I'll speak for myself.

235
00:22:07.010 --> 00:22:10.388
Like you. I've lost blood.
Like you. I haven't eaten in days.

236
00:22:10.472 --> 00:22:12.474
And although I haven't been whipped
on the rack like you...

237
00:22:12.557 --> 00:22:13.767
Shh! Tamacti.

238
00:22:17.771 --> 00:22:21.358
- What do you see. my love?
- Cages of the God bone.

239
00:22:22.359 --> 00:22:24.402
- Shit.
- What?

240
00:22:25.195 --> 00:22:26.530
It's a Slaver's den.

241
00:22:27.280 --> 00:22:30.534
- You know this place from before?
- No. I do not.

242
00:22:30.617 --> 00:22:32.410
Tamacti. we must move quickly. Come.

243
00:22:32.494 --> 00:22:34.829
Papa. it's okay. There's no one coming.

244
00:22:36.540 --> 00:22:37.791
They're already here.

245
00:22:42.754 --> 00:22:44.464
Stand where you are.

246
00:22:45.590 --> 00:22:47.092
Greetings. friend.

247
00:22:48.343 --> 00:22:50.679
If we are trespassing. I apologize.

248
00:22:51.346 --> 00:22:54.307
We have no intentions other than
to get to the eastern foothills.

249
00:22:54.891 --> 00:22:57.102
What's your business in the foothills?

250
00:22:57.894 --> 00:22:59.688
The Yuree cattle markets.

251
00:23:03.275 --> 00:23:04.401
You may go.

252
00:23:04.901 --> 00:23:06.528
Thank you.

253
00:23:11.032 --> 00:23:12.576
Not you. girl.

254
00:23:12.659 --> 00:23:13.743
Papa!

255
00:23:31.094 --> 00:23:32.095
Papa!

256
00:23:37.684 --> 00:23:40.770
You'll be taught obedience. girl.

257
00:24:51.132 --> 00:24:53.718
Who's there? Speak!

258
00:24:53.802 --> 00:24:56.263
Catch your breath. Baba. You are safe.

259
00:24:56.346 --> 00:24:57.347
Paris!

260
00:24:57.430 --> 00:24:58.431
Haniwa!

261
00:25:01.518 --> 00:25:04.396
- Paris. Who fights with us?
- Baba.

262
00:25:04.479 --> 00:25:07.065
I will explain more
when we are somewhere safe.

263
00:25:07.148 --> 00:25:09.693
- Where's Kofun?
- Kofun has gone on to Pennsa.

264
00:25:09.776 --> 00:25:11.444
And I have important news.

265
00:25:11.945 --> 00:25:13.280
Maghra is alive.

266
00:25:13.363 --> 00:25:14.781
- You've heard?
- Yes.

267
00:25:15.991 --> 00:25:17.534
You should've went with Kofun.

268
00:25:17.617 --> 00:25:20.579
Well. then where would you be now.
you big lump?

269
00:25:20.662 --> 00:25:22.038
- We'll go now.
- No.

270
00:25:22.122 --> 00:25:23.665
You're not fit to travel.

271
00:25:24.165 --> 00:25:26.251
I hear deep pain in your voice.

272
00:25:26.334 --> 00:25:29.171
You must rest and heal
before we can make this journey.

273
00:25:29.254 --> 00:25:30.255
Baba Voss.

274
00:25:32.841 --> 00:25:33.967
Paris. wait.

275
00:25:34.050 --> 00:25:35.260
- Tamacti Jun.
- Paris.

276
00:25:36.803 --> 00:25:38.972
The Witchfinder general.

277
00:25:39.055 --> 00:25:40.348
What a find.

278
00:25:40.432 --> 00:25:42.893
After we kill him.
I'll keep his ears as a trophy.

279
00:25:42.976 --> 00:25:44.895
No. We need his help.

280
00:25:45.645 --> 00:25:47.814
We never would have made it
out of Trivantes without him.

281
00:25:47.898 --> 00:25:50.567
- He's no longer one of them.
- Even if that were true...

282
00:25:50.650 --> 00:25:55.280
He can track the queen's soldiers.
He's helping me find Maghra.

283
00:25:55.363 --> 00:25:57.699
We are not bringing
a Witchfinder home with us.

284
00:25:57.782 --> 00:26:00.869
We're not going anywhere with you.
We're going to Pennsa.

285
00:26:00.952 --> 00:26:05.665
Haniwa. your father needs rest.
Even now. his breath fails him.

286
00:26:06.750 --> 00:26:07.751
Papa.

287
00:26:11.213 --> 00:26:12.464
Where is this home?

288
00:26:12.964 --> 00:26:15.175
It does not matter.
We are going straight to Pennsa.

289
00:26:15.675 --> 00:26:18.136
Baba. we have made camp nearby.

290
00:26:18.762 --> 00:26:21.473
Rest for the night.
Then we go on to Pennsa from there.

291
00:26:21.556 --> 00:26:24.434
You cannot really mean
that we will travel with the Witchfinder.

292
00:26:24.518 --> 00:26:27.395
Where we go. he goes. Yes?

293
00:26:27.896 --> 00:26:28.939
So be it.

294
00:26:29.689 --> 00:26:31.733
Vienna. Quito. return home.

295
00:26:32.442 --> 00:26:34.986
Inform them
that we are going on to Pennsa.

296
00:26:35.070 --> 00:26:36.738
Charlotte. to the camp.

297
00:26:45.163 --> 00:26:47.832
Some 200 years ago.

298
00:26:47.916 --> 00:26:52.879
a small number of Payan children
were born with vision.

299
00:26:54.422 --> 00:26:59.010
Their mothers fled to the mountains
to hide them from the Witchfinders.

300
00:27:00.345 --> 00:27:04.850
But eventually they were found and burned.

301
00:27:07.561 --> 00:27:10.438
Those grieving mothers formed the Compass.

302
00:27:11.773 --> 00:27:14.192
It's a secret society of guardians

303
00:27:14.693 --> 00:27:18.029
whose membership is passed on
from mother to daughter.

304
00:27:19.573 --> 00:27:22.409
We've remained a secret for generations.

305
00:27:22.909 --> 00:27:25.787
standing by.
ready to take on the sacred duty

306
00:27:25.871 --> 00:27:28.623
of protecting the sighted
when vision returns.

307
00:27:29.207 --> 00:27:31.209
And how many sighted children
have you met?

308
00:27:32.669 --> 00:27:35.380
Counting you? One.

309
00:27:35.463 --> 00:27:38.300
And that is one more
than my mother or her mother met.

310
00:27:38.383 --> 00:27:41.052
I never imagined it
would happen in my lifetime. but it has.

311
00:27:42.387 --> 00:27:44.472
Paris. what do you have to do with them?

312
00:27:47.726 --> 00:27:51.354
That is a long story. And a sad one.

313
00:27:53.356 --> 00:27:54.858
You were one of them.

314
00:27:57.736 --> 00:28:00.655
Yes. I was.

315
00:28:05.994 --> 00:28:07.412
A lifetime ago.

316
00:28:08.914 --> 00:28:11.416
No one ever blamed you. Paris.

317
00:28:11.499 --> 00:28:14.878
Nevertheless. it was my responsibility.

318
00:28:16.546 --> 00:28:19.424
The curse of every Presage I've ever met.

319
00:28:19.508 --> 00:28:22.844
You all think you're responsible
for knowing everything before it happens.

320
00:28:24.763 --> 00:28:28.058
Is it true that Queen Kane decreed
the sighted are no longer witches?

321
00:28:28.683 --> 00:28:29.893
That's the talk.

322
00:28:29.976 --> 00:28:33.271
This queen's
proclamation is ill-conceived.

323
00:28:33.355 --> 00:28:36.525
Bigotry cannot be changed by decree.

324
00:28:37.192 --> 00:28:39.361
If anything. she's made you
even more of a target.

325
00:28:43.823 --> 00:28:46.409
Which may be as she intended.

326
00:28:55.293 --> 00:28:56.920
I guess he needed to sleep.

327
00:28:57.003 --> 00:28:58.505
So do I.

328
00:28:58.588 --> 00:29:02.092
Which is why I put enough valerian root
in his ale to knock out a horse.

329
00:29:02.175 --> 00:29:05.971
'Cause if he's not snoring.
I'm up all night with my ropes in my hand.

330
00:29:06.638 --> 00:29:08.056
More grub anybody?

331
00:29:12.102 --> 00:29:14.688
Come on. Toad.
You took the same oath we did.

332
00:29:14.771 --> 00:29:17.190
To seek out and destroy
the witches no matter the cost.

333
00:29:17.274 --> 00:29:19.442
We serve the queen. Dax.
We follow her orders.

334
00:29:19.526 --> 00:29:21.027
Not when the orders are heresy.

335
00:29:21.111 --> 00:29:23.738
God Flame first. Queen second.

336
00:29:23.822 --> 00:29:26.074
Dax is right. This feels wrong.

337
00:29:26.575 --> 00:29:29.160
- We're breaking the law.
- We've been tasked with his safety.

338
00:29:29.953 --> 00:29:31.705
He's the queen's nephew.

339
00:29:31.788 --> 00:29:34.082
What do you think she'll do
to the man who harms him?

340
00:29:34.165 --> 00:29:35.917
We cannot ride into Pennsa with a witch.

341
00:29:36.001 --> 00:29:37.961
we'll be shunned or burned
as heretics right beside him.

342
00:29:38.044 --> 00:29:38.879
Don't be an idiot.

343
00:29:38.962 --> 00:29:40.630
We should be gutting him.
not escorting him.

344
00:29:40.714 --> 00:29:42.591
You don't wanna kill him?
Fine. don't kill him.

345
00:29:42.674 --> 00:29:44.509
Let's just leave him here
and say he ran away.

346
00:29:44.593 --> 00:29:45.677
Let the forest have him.

347
00:29:45.760 --> 00:29:48.346
Come on. Toad. You know he's right.

348
00:29:48.430 --> 00:29:49.431
No.

349
00:29:49.973 --> 00:29:53.977
What he is is one word away from
an insubordination charge and a demotion.

350
00:29:54.477 --> 00:29:56.563
And he'll take you right down with him.

351
00:29:57.731 --> 00:30:00.233
Shut your mouths and do your fucking jobs.

352
00:30:01.359 --> 00:30:02.611
And if you're lucky.

353
00:30:03.111 --> 00:30:06.239
I'll forget this conversation happened
by the time we reach Pennsa.

354
00:30:54.621 --> 00:30:56.456
You should announce yourself.

355
00:30:56.540 --> 00:30:57.999
Apologies. Princess.

356
00:30:58.083 --> 00:31:00.418
I keep forgetting
it's not my house anymore.

357
00:31:02.796 --> 00:31:05.215
Whistle sword. weapon of kings.

358
00:31:05.715 --> 00:31:07.008
And their daughters.

359
00:31:08.093 --> 00:31:09.219
You sent for me?

360
00:31:09.928 --> 00:31:10.929
Yes. I did.

361
00:31:12.180 --> 00:31:16.935
- This marriage proposal of yours...
- I made no such proposal.

362
00:31:17.018 --> 00:31:18.854
Well. my sister did it for you.

363
00:31:19.604 --> 00:31:21.481
That is unfortunate.

364
00:31:21.565 --> 00:31:24.067
Let me assure you.
I had something more romantic in mind.

365
00:31:24.150 --> 00:31:27.028
- I have a husband.
- We all have our flaws.

366
00:31:27.904 --> 00:31:31.116
I tend to snore if I sleep on my back.
But piece of advice...

367
00:31:31.199 --> 00:31:33.159
- Harlan. Harlan.
- …a swift kick will usually shut me up.

368
00:31:33.243 --> 00:31:34.619
- so I'm told.
- Harlan!

369
00:31:36.413 --> 00:31:37.998
What is it you're really after?

370
00:31:50.552 --> 00:31:52.762
I come from a rich tradition of men

371
00:31:53.847 --> 00:31:56.766
who fought for crumbs
at the feet of the monarchy.

372
00:31:59.519 --> 00:32:05.192
Now. I worked tirelessly for many years

373
00:32:06.151 --> 00:32:08.653
to get something better for myself.

374
00:32:11.573 --> 00:32:13.575
It took some doing. believe me.

375
00:32:14.159 --> 00:32:16.703
And now. in walks the queen.

376
00:32:17.621 --> 00:32:21.124
and she screws it all up
with this war of hers.

377
00:32:21.208 --> 00:32:23.627
And I find myself with two choices.

378
00:32:25.003 --> 00:32:29.132
One: I stoke the fires of rebellion
and burn down the whole palace.

379
00:32:30.550 --> 00:32:34.221
or two: I join you and move into it.

380
00:32:37.599 --> 00:32:42.062
After much consideration. Princess.
I've reached a conclusion.

381
00:32:43.355 --> 00:32:45.148
Number two is a lot less work.

382
00:32:47.359 --> 00:32:49.152
You're wooing the wrong sister.

383
00:32:49.778 --> 00:32:52.906
- I'm wooing the better sister.
- Sibeth is the one with the power.

384
00:32:53.573 --> 00:32:54.783
For now.

385
00:33:05.710 --> 00:33:08.338
- We will announce an engagement.
- Excellent.

386
00:33:08.421 --> 00:33:09.548
But there will be no wedding.

387
00:33:10.257 --> 00:33:11.883
Not to put too fine a point on it...

388
00:33:11.967 --> 00:33:14.261
The engagement will ease
my sister's concerns

389
00:33:14.344 --> 00:33:16.513
about Kanzua for the time being.

390
00:33:17.389 --> 00:33:19.391
You will use your influence
with the council

391
00:33:19.474 --> 00:33:21.643
to help me stop her from going to war.

392
00:33:22.227 --> 00:33:24.980
And once my husband
and my daughter are found.

393
00:33:25.480 --> 00:33:28.859
you will make sure
that they are protected at all costs.

394
00:33:32.571 --> 00:33:33.738
And in exchange?

395
00:33:35.657 --> 00:33:39.661
I will convince Sibeth to make her capital
in a more suitable city.

396
00:33:39.744 --> 00:33:41.955
and you will have yours back.

397
00:33:44.708 --> 00:33:45.709
Maghra.

398
00:33:47.586 --> 00:33:49.546
I believe I underestimated you.

399
00:33:51.173 --> 00:33:53.008
Well. I hope I've done the same.

400
00:33:53.800 --> 00:33:55.302
Time will tell. Princess.

401
00:34:28.126 --> 00:34:30.378
- Chet-chet.
- Chet-chet.

402
00:34:34.716 --> 00:34:36.009
Hot tea.

403
00:34:47.354 --> 00:34:50.982
So. you were a Compass warrior?

404
00:34:52.400 --> 00:34:56.196
Guardian.
Lost the appetite for it long ago.

405
00:35:00.283 --> 00:35:01.493
Why did you leave?

406
00:35:08.333 --> 00:35:14.130
When I was with the Compass. Haniwa.
it was a thrilling time.

407
00:35:15.090 --> 00:35:19.094
Two hundred years without reports
of a sighted child.

408
00:35:19.177 --> 00:35:23.181
and then suddenly there appeared a boy.

409
00:35:24.599 --> 00:35:26.768
I was assigned to protect him.

410
00:35:27.268 --> 00:35:29.728
He was gifted beyond his sight.

411
00:35:29.813 --> 00:35:34.568
I mean. his young mind
just cried out for knowledge…

412
00:35:36.277 --> 00:35:37.612
like yours did.

413
00:35:41.699 --> 00:35:42.951
I broke the rules.

414
00:35:45.078 --> 00:35:48.581
I allowed him access
to the artifacts we stored.

415
00:35:48.665 --> 00:35:49.666
Books…

416
00:35:51.458 --> 00:35:54.420
And the knotted codes
that would teach him to read.

417
00:35:55.672 --> 00:36:00.385
Soon. I couldn't find enough books
to satisfy his hunger for knowledge.

418
00:36:02.137 --> 00:36:04.639
I woke up one day and he was gone.

419
00:36:05.473 --> 00:36:09.060
along with the books
and the knotted codes.

420
00:36:13.315 --> 00:36:15.066
I failed the Compass.

421
00:36:16.318 --> 00:36:20.363
I failed in the thing
that I was sworn to do.

422
00:36:21.489 --> 00:36:24.242
So I did the only thing I could. I left.

423
00:36:30.248 --> 00:36:33.835
Do you know what became of him? The boy?

424
00:36:39.007 --> 00:36:41.176
He became your father.

425
00:36:52.896 --> 00:36:54.064
Jerlamarel.

426
00:36:55.106 --> 00:36:56.107
Yes.

427
00:36:59.194 --> 00:37:03.114
Years later. as your mother carried you.
Jerlamarel found me.

428
00:37:03.615 --> 00:37:05.075
He knew I was Alkenny.

429
00:37:05.992 --> 00:37:10.705
He knew I would protect
and guide his children.

430
00:37:11.498 --> 00:37:13.583
And make sure we knew how to read.

431
00:37:16.837 --> 00:37:19.256
I'm hoping that was the right choice.

432
00:37:26.137 --> 00:37:27.389
Of course it was.

433
00:37:28.765 --> 00:37:32.727
Sight is as much a part of me

434
00:37:34.229 --> 00:37:37.190
as your hands are a part of you.

435
00:37:39.568 --> 00:37:41.903
It would be wrong for me not to read.

436
00:37:47.534 --> 00:37:48.743
Dear one…

437
00:37:51.162 --> 00:37:54.457
Humankind has a long history...

438
00:37:55.208 --> 00:38:00.922
A long history of despising and fearing
those who are different.

439
00:38:01.923 --> 00:38:03.592
Nobody chooses how they're born.

440
00:38:04.926 --> 00:38:09.222
And yet the unsighted persecute
the sighted.

441
00:38:13.810 --> 00:38:19.441
If one day the sighted outnumber
the unsighted again.

442
00:38:20.525 --> 00:38:22.235
the roles will reverse.

443
00:38:24.154 --> 00:38:29.034
It is one of the many ways
in which we all are very much the same.

444
00:39:01.942 --> 00:39:03.109
What are you doing?

445
00:39:03.193 --> 00:39:04.611
My job. witch.

446
00:39:05.320 --> 00:39:06.905
- Toad!
- Shut up.

447
00:39:07.405 --> 00:39:08.406
Hold him still!

448
00:39:14.788 --> 00:39:16.206
Come on. witch!

449
00:39:20.836 --> 00:39:21.878
Toad!

450
00:39:34.224 --> 00:39:37.811
Dax! Frye! What the fuck are you doing?

451
00:39:37.894 --> 00:39:39.145
Fall in!

452
00:39:42.566 --> 00:39:43.400
Toad!

453
00:39:47.571 --> 00:39:49.281
Frye! Stop. Frye.

454
00:39:49.781 --> 00:39:51.616
Toad! Toad!

455
00:39:51.700 --> 00:39:53.660
Toad! Toad! Toad!

456
00:39:55.871 --> 00:39:57.956
Toad! Toad!

457
00:39:58.039 --> 00:40:00.041
Toad! Toad!

458
00:40:04.045 --> 00:40:06.965
Toad. Toad.

459
00:40:07.465 --> 00:40:10.218
- Dax. Dax!
- Toad.

460
00:40:12.387 --> 00:40:13.388
Frye?

461
00:40:15.223 --> 00:40:16.224
Frye?

462
00:40:17.893 --> 00:40:19.728
- Frye!
- Stay down. Dax.

463
00:40:20.812 --> 00:40:21.813
What'd you do?

464
00:40:22.939 --> 00:40:24.316
Stay the fuck down.

465
00:40:25.650 --> 00:40:26.568
You killed him.

466
00:40:27.152 --> 00:40:29.196
And I'll kill you too
if you don't stand down right now.

467
00:40:30.906 --> 00:40:34.242
What's wrong with you?
You're a Witchfinder protecting a witch!

468
00:40:34.326 --> 00:40:36.661
I'm not gonna tell you again. Dax!

469
00:40:36.745 --> 00:40:38.872
Stand the fuck down! Now!

470
00:40:44.127 --> 00:40:45.212
I'm leaving.

471
00:40:46.213 --> 00:40:47.964
I want no part of this.

472
00:40:48.048 --> 00:40:50.091
If you wanna desert.
take your horse and go.

473
00:40:50.675 --> 00:40:52.427
But if you attempt to interfere
with this mission.

474
00:40:52.511 --> 00:40:54.262
I will kill you where you stand.

475
00:41:23.500 --> 00:41:25.210
- Toad.
- Shut up.

476
00:41:33.844 --> 00:41:35.136
Can you ride a horse?

477
00:41:37.848 --> 00:41:38.849
Not really.

478
00:41:41.393 --> 00:41:42.978
Well. I hope you're a quick learner.

479
00:41:45.605 --> 00:41:47.065
'Cause you're not riding with me.

480
00:42:12.507 --> 00:42:15.010
Why didn't you kill Edo
when you had the chance?

481
00:42:19.598 --> 00:42:23.476
Killing a brother would be
like killing a part of yourself.

482
00:42:26.938 --> 00:42:28.648
Like killing your own father?

483
00:42:39.701 --> 00:42:42.495
My father ordered me to kill Edo.

484
00:42:44.664 --> 00:42:46.082
And I made a choice.

485
00:42:53.882 --> 00:42:57.219
If you were protecting Edo.
then why does he hate you so much?

486
00:43:02.015 --> 00:43:05.560
Family can be complicated.

487
00:43:12.943 --> 00:43:13.818
Well…

488
00:43:15.320 --> 00:43:19.199
I was just kidnapped by my uncle

489
00:43:19.282 --> 00:43:22.494
and found out that my mom is a princess.

490
00:43:25.497 --> 00:43:28.625
I think I know something
about complicated families.

491
00:43:40.178 --> 00:43:42.430
My mother died giving birth to Edo.

492
00:43:44.683 --> 00:43:46.852
And my father never forgave him for that.

493
00:43:47.978 --> 00:43:51.606
I was just a young boy.
almost too young to remember her.

494
00:43:53.608 --> 00:43:56.319
And too young
to question my father's point of view.

495
00:44:08.999 --> 00:44:10.333
You asked for me. sir?

496
00:44:13.587 --> 00:44:15.547
The girl. Haniwa. is an archer.

497
00:44:17.549 --> 00:44:18.675
Is she?

498
00:44:19.634 --> 00:44:21.511
She put three arrows in me.

499
00:44:23.680 --> 00:44:27.142
My brother has raised
two of Jerlamarel's children.

500
00:44:27.642 --> 00:44:29.895
That is a dangerous combination.

501
00:44:32.063 --> 00:44:36.818
A group of Slavers was killed
at a den in Munhall today.

502
00:44:38.403 --> 00:44:39.779
You think it was them?

503
00:44:43.116 --> 00:44:46.328
Baba's hurt. He's tired.
He won't be moving very fast.

504
00:44:47.871 --> 00:44:50.207
Send word to every outpost in the area…

505
00:44:51.791 --> 00:44:55.921
That I want Baba and the girl
brought back to me alive.

506
00:44:58.548 --> 00:44:59.382
Yes. sir.

507
00:45:00.634 --> 00:45:01.635
Lieutenant?

508
00:45:13.188 --> 00:45:16.399
Any word on who helped them escape?

509
00:45:19.402 --> 00:45:20.695
No. sir. Nothing yet.

510
00:45:24.699 --> 00:45:28.036
That's odd. Wren. That's very odd.

511
00:45:31.831 --> 00:45:34.167
But I think
I might have an idea about that.

512
00:45:36.503 --> 00:45:37.754
Keep me informed.

513
00:45:38.588 --> 00:45:39.589
Yes. sir.

514
00:45:59.359 --> 00:46:01.319
- Toad.
- What?

515
00:46:05.949 --> 00:46:07.659
Thank you for saving my life.

516
00:46:11.621 --> 00:46:13.456
Your gratitude is misplaced.

517
00:46:14.749 --> 00:46:17.836
You're Princess Maghra's son.
and I'm duty bound to protect you.

518
00:46:19.421 --> 00:46:20.630
I had no choice.

519
00:46:25.802 --> 00:46:27.345
You had a choice.

520
00:46:55.540 --> 00:46:56.708
Give me the map.

521
00:47:13.266 --> 00:47:16.978
It'll take 13 days to get to Pennsa
if the weather holds.

522
00:47:17.479 --> 00:47:19.564
We can get there in half that time.

523
00:47:19.648 --> 00:47:21.399
What? How?

524
00:47:23.443 --> 00:47:24.444
This way.

525
00:47:29.449 --> 00:47:30.742
There's a cliff.

526
00:47:31.368 --> 00:47:33.662
Yes. according to the map.

527
00:47:33.745 --> 00:47:36.498
But there is no cliff.
We can go straight through.

528
00:47:36.581 --> 00:47:37.582
And how do you know that?

529
00:47:38.542 --> 00:47:40.001
They make the maps.

530
00:47:40.877 --> 00:47:42.379
That's how we've kept our outpost

531
00:47:42.462 --> 00:47:45.382
hidden all these centuries
from bastards like you.

532
00:47:46.758 --> 00:47:47.759
Haniwa?

533
00:47:48.260 --> 00:47:51.721
I am charged
with your protection at any cost.

534
00:47:52.389 --> 00:47:55.767
You will always stay behind me.

535
00:47:56.476 --> 00:47:58.854
Always behind me.

536
00:47:59.521 --> 00:48:03.149
Your father always behind you.

537
00:48:03.233 --> 00:48:05.610
I don't need a guardian.
I can take care of myself.

538
00:48:06.945 --> 00:48:09.698
You were almost made
a breeding machine in Trivantes.

539
00:48:09.781 --> 00:48:11.074
And I got out.

540
00:48:11.157 --> 00:48:13.159
And nearly lost your head
at a Slaver's camp.

541
00:48:13.243 --> 00:48:15.245
At this rate.
I expect you'll be dead within the week.

542
00:48:16.121 --> 00:48:17.205
Haniwa.

543
00:48:22.043 --> 00:48:23.628
Just don't get in my way.

544
00:48:24.212 --> 00:48:26.548
You're the sighted one. Don't get in mine.

545
00:48:28.717 --> 00:48:31.970
Always behind me.
Your father always behind you.

546
00:48:34.723 --> 00:48:35.807
Paris.

547
00:48:42.105 --> 00:48:43.273
Jasmine.

548
00:48:48.737 --> 00:48:50.530
Burnt sage.

549
00:48:59.039 --> 00:49:03.126
Rain across the meadows.

550
00:49:05.879 --> 00:49:08.173
Thank you. Your Majesty.

551
00:49:12.844 --> 00:49:18.558
I had heard that the Pennsan Scent Chefs
were among the best in the land.

552
00:49:19.726 --> 00:49:21.561
And now I know it to be true.

553
00:49:23.104 --> 00:49:26.816
I hope you all enjoyed the performance.

554
00:49:28.527 --> 00:49:32.822
I've learned
that even in our darkest hours.

555
00:49:33.406 --> 00:49:37.285
we must find time
to appreciate the beauty and joy

556
00:49:37.369 --> 00:49:39.579
with which the God Flame blesses us.

557
00:49:39.663 --> 00:49:43.583
Even now.
with the struggle that lies ahead.

558
00:49:44.167 --> 00:49:45.836
there is beauty to be found.

559
00:49:47.003 --> 00:49:49.840
There is love.

560
00:49:51.341 --> 00:49:53.385
And so it is with great joy

561
00:49:53.468 --> 00:49:56.638
that I share with you.
the esteemed members of my court.

562
00:49:57.138 --> 00:50:02.853
that my sister. Princess Maghra Kane.
has been betrothed

563
00:50:03.353 --> 00:50:08.400
to none other than your very own
Lord Harlan of Pennsa.

564
00:50:09.776 --> 00:50:12.112
I thought we were going to announce this.

565
00:50:12.195 --> 00:50:13.655
Yeah. I thought so too.

566
00:50:13.738 --> 00:50:16.366
And we will all bear witness
to their marriage

567
00:50:17.200 --> 00:50:20.036
on the fourth God Flame rising from today.

568
00:50:22.080 --> 00:50:23.123
We are Payan.

569
00:50:23.206 --> 00:50:25.166
- Were you part of this?
- No.

570
00:50:25.250 --> 00:50:26.293
We are holy

571
00:50:26.376 --> 00:50:28.003
I'm not sure I believe you.

572
00:50:28.503 --> 00:50:32.424
Well. Princess. at some point.
you're gonna have to trust me.

573
00:50:33.425 --> 00:50:35.218
You better give me a reason to.

574
00:50:35.302 --> 00:50:37.762
We are chosen.

575
00:50:44.394 --> 00:50:45.604
Father.

576
00:50:48.690 --> 00:50:49.774
What is it?

577
00:50:50.275 --> 00:50:51.526
The general is here.

578
00:50:52.944 --> 00:50:53.945
What?

579
00:50:55.697 --> 00:50:56.948
Edo Voss is here?

580
00:50:57.532 --> 00:51:00.285
He just arrived with some soldiers.

581
00:51:04.039 --> 00:51:06.374
He must not know that I am compromised.

582
00:51:12.422 --> 00:51:15.884
General Voss. This is quite a surprise.

583
00:51:16.843 --> 00:51:17.928
Really?

584
00:51:21.723 --> 00:51:23.642
I half thought you'd be expecting me.

585
00:51:25.602 --> 00:51:26.603
And why's that?

586
00:51:32.025 --> 00:51:36.488
Someone walked into my prison
and walked out with Baba Voss.

587
00:51:38.365 --> 00:51:39.908
You captured Baba Voss?

588
00:51:42.077 --> 00:51:43.078
We had him.

589
00:51:44.955 --> 00:51:46.206
Until we didn't.

590
00:51:47.541 --> 00:51:50.210
It's no small thing
to outmaneuver the guards

591
00:51:50.710 --> 00:51:53.505
and navigate passages
of a Trivantian prison

592
00:51:54.756 --> 00:51:58.844
unless one has the gift of sight.

593
00:52:00.345 --> 00:52:05.183
And you are accusing me?
Why in the world would I free Baba Voss?

594
00:52:05.267 --> 00:52:06.434
Where's the son?

595
00:52:08.061 --> 00:52:09.062
The son?

596
00:52:10.313 --> 00:52:13.316
The son you refused to send
with my men when they were here.

597
00:52:13.650 --> 00:52:15.694
- I'd like him now.
- Listen to me.

598
00:52:15.777 --> 00:52:18.488
The trap you set brought
Baba Voss to my door.

599
00:52:18.572 --> 00:52:21.992
He killed my guards
and took my son by force.

600
00:52:22.742 --> 00:52:25.287
Baba Voss was here and he left you alive?

601
00:52:27.038 --> 00:52:29.457
Even after you gave away his daughter?

602
00:52:32.002 --> 00:52:33.336
He had no choice. He was outnumbered.

603
00:52:36.464 --> 00:52:38.925
What is this? What is this?

604
00:52:39.009 --> 00:52:45.140
And why does the boy answer
when I am speaking to the father?

605
00:52:46.516 --> 00:52:49.853
And why aren't you moving
around like you usually do when we meet.

606
00:52:50.854 --> 00:52:52.480
to lord your gift over me?

607
00:52:54.482 --> 00:52:55.984
It's almost as if...

608
00:52:56.067 --> 00:52:58.403
Listen. General.
if you came all this way. just...

609
00:52:59.404 --> 00:53:01.615
Let him go! Let him go.

610
00:53:01.698 --> 00:53:04.034
- General.
- Quiet.

611
00:53:19.424 --> 00:53:20.842
He took your sight.

612
00:53:22.719 --> 00:53:24.221
A temporary injury.

613
00:53:24.971 --> 00:53:27.307
One that will soon be healed.

614
00:53:31.520 --> 00:53:32.521
No.

615
00:53:35.398 --> 00:53:36.483
It will not.

616
00:53:40.028 --> 00:53:41.404
No!

617
00:53:41.488 --> 00:53:43.615
No! No!

618
00:53:44.115 --> 00:53:47.118
No! No!

619
00:53:48.161 --> 00:53:52.332
I will kill you.
I swear to God. I will kill you.

620
00:53:53.708 --> 00:53:55.460
Put aside your grief. Oloman.

621
00:53:56.711 --> 00:53:59.506
It falls on you now
to protect the rest of your family.

622
00:54:00.090 --> 00:54:03.385
To do that. you'll need a clear head.

623
00:54:04.302 --> 00:54:06.596
This house belongs to me now.

624
00:54:07.514 --> 00:54:11.226
You. the books. the knowledge. all of it.

625
00:54:12.519 --> 00:54:13.562
Tormada!

626
00:54:22.362 --> 00:54:26.116
This is Tormada.
He's one of our greatest scientists.

627
00:54:28.577 --> 00:54:29.870
You work for him now.

